ce:section.ce:para:
In this work, we developed a novel, environmentally friendly, and harmless ratiometric fluorescent nanosensor by encapsulating green fluorescent nitrogen-doped carbon dots (N-CDs) within the interior of the mSiO2, which serves as the internal reference signal for fluorescence. The external amide-branched red fluorescent BSA-AuNCs provide the fluorescence response signal. The ratio of the fluorescence signals at 650 nm and 520 nm (F650/F520
                     ) for this ratiometric fluorescent nanosensor decreases with increasing Co2+ concentration, resulting in a fluorescence color change from yellow to green. In addition, we recorded the RGB values of the fluorescent sensors under UV lamps at different Co2+ concentrations using a smartphone mobile RGB color extractor, incorporating the LightGBM algorithm. The detection of Co2+ in soil is both rapid, taking less than 10 s, and accurate. Scheme 1
                      represents the first instance of a fluorescent nanosensor being integrated with the LightGBM algorithm to achieve low-cost, environmentally friendly, and rapid detection of Co2+ in soil.
